%I A395073 #36 Jun 16 2026 14:35:04
%S A395073 1,1,3,14,146,5640
%N A395073 Number of nonisomorphic join-hull commutative convexities on a set of n elements.
%C A395073 A convexity C on a set X is a collection of subsets of X such that {} and X are in C, C is closed under arbitrary intersection, and C is closed under directed union.
%C A395073 Every subset S under a convexity C admits a minimal convex superset, which we denote by conv(S). A convexity C is said to be join-hull commutative (JHC) if for all p in X and A in C, the union of conv({p,x}) over x in A is a convex set.
%C A395073 By an isomorphism f: (X,C) -> (Y,D) of convexities, it is understood a map f so that A in C <=> f(A) in D for all subsets A of X.
%H A395073 Victor Chepoi, <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/2407147_Separation_Of_Two_Convex_Sets_In_Convexity_Structures">Separation of Two Convex Sets in Convexity Structures</a>
%H A395073 Tian Vlasic, <a href="/A395073/a395073.py.txt">Python program</a>
%H A395073 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Closure_operator">Closure operator</a>
%F A395073 It is well known that every JHC convexity is interval, hence a(n) <= A367422(n).
%e A395073 The a(3) = 14 set-systems are the following (system {{}, {1,2,3}}, and sets {} and {1,2,3} are omitted).
